    public class SearchController
extends com.usersmarts.cx.web.AbstractConnectorController
    The Search Service provides UICDS clients with services to discover and access work products using OpenSearch enabled feeds. The Search Service accepts Google-style query strings via the q parameter. For instance: 
         ?q=productType=incident&updatedBy=bob
    The table follow describes the supported query terms. Boolean (true or false) indicator of the Work Product status
    Term Description
    productID The identifier of a Work Product
    productType The type of a Work Product
    productVersion The version of a Work Product
    createdDate The date and time the Work Product was created
    createdBy The name of the user that created the Work Product
    updatedDate The date and time the Work Product was last updated
    updatedBy The name of the user that last updated the Work Product
    active
    cyber.protocol Any internet protocol (HTTP, FTP, etc) contained in the Work Product metadata
    cyber.address Any internet address contained in the Work Product metadata
    digest.event.descriptor The textual description of an event contained in the Work Product metadata
    where.minx The West boundary of bounding box of all location information contained within the Work Product Metadata
    where.maxx The East boundary of bounding box of all location information contained within the Work Product Metadata
    where.miny The South boundary of bounding box of all location information contained within the Work Product Metadata
    where.maxy The North boundary of bounding box of all location information contained within the Work Product Metadata
    where.city Any city name referenced within the Work Product metadata
    where.postalCode Any postal code referenced within the Work Product metadata
    where.province Any province name referenced within the Work Product metadata
    where.state Any state name referenced within the Work Product metadata
    where.street Any street address referenced within the Work Product metadata, including the street number
    where.countryCode Any count code referenced within the Work Product metadata
    digest.event.what The type of any "Thing" referenced within the Work Product metadata
    The format of the results is controlled by the format parameter. For instance: 
         ?q=productType=incident&updatedBy=bob&format=atom
    Currently supported formats:
    Format Description
    atom Atom Syndication Format with GeoRSS GML extensions
    rss RSS 2.0 with W3C Basic Geo extensions
    Author:
    Christopher Lakey idd -- remove it from IDD by DDH
    See Also:
    OpenSearch 1.1 Specification, The Atom Syndication Format, RSS 2.0 Specification, GeoRSS Specification, W3C Basic Geo Vocabulary
